<br>
I am NOT conservative.<br>
I am NOT Liberal<br>
I am NOT Democrat, Republican, Libritarian, or Whig, gay, St. Bernard hugger, or whatever other group you can try to stick me with.  If anything, I am probably closest to Ted Nuget style Anarchist than any other single party out there.  So, why do I bring this up?<br>
<br>
In many ways I agree with Maus's point, but in many others, I do not (which is no surprise).  To gloss it over, communities SHOULD have the ultimate power to deal with their offenders in any way they see fit.  If they want to execute you for having sexual relations with your 92 year-old grandmother... then PERHAPS you should consider moving.<br>
Laws are made by people trying to play god under the illusion of maintaining order.  Penalties are created, ultimately, to generate revenue to support the legal system.  Mankind has a nature to gravitate to an organized society, so the megatropolises many of you live in are an unavoidable consequence... and the laws required to sustain them are also unavoidable.  The legal system, therefore, will happen.. no matter what we do.<br>
<br>
That this woman should be beat to death with ball-peen hammers is, in my opinion, obvious.  Because of our legal system that is plauged with both conservative AND liberal special intereasts, this would NEVER take place (legaly).  Unfortunately, the laws we live by are made to protect people like her, NOT people like you, Maus, and even me.  Speaking personally, I would like to just live my life in quiet solitude, pay my taxes when they are due, buy my food as needed, and talk to the microscopic group of people I call friends when I feel inclined to do so.<br>
The laws made to protect women LIKE this are most of the reason I have little respect for our legal system.  Between Hobbes and Locke, it has all been explained... you just have to decide how far to which side of the fence (or wheel) you stand on.<br>
<br>
So what about giving the state power over your reproductive system?  What about telling people WHEN they are allowed to reproduce?  Ask yourself, especially those of you with kids, are you SURE you would want to give this power to your government?  I am sure Maus can tell you about countless headaches he has had to endure through VA hospitals (assuming you go to VA hospitals), so are you SURE you would want to make this a requirement to have a child?  If we were talking about simply a license... would this help, or further complicate the problem?  If you can have kids without a required license... and do.... what then?  <br>
<br>
Personally, I like to think people like this will weed themselves out.  The problem with this theory is that we as a society can't finish the job.  She has killed her child, so part of the chain is broken, but the legal system will protect her and her rights to polute the world with more of her offspring.  Now, if her neighbors could kill her in a rousing mob-style burning... the job would be completed. <br>
<br>
Oh, by the way ... she didn't forget her kid in the car (if I read this correctly).  The kid was left unsupervised and locked herself in the car.  My guess would be that she went to sleep and the heat killed her.  Ultimately, she killed herself.<br>
<br>
It's Darwinism in action. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://guildmagic.com/character.cfm?ID=316564" target="top">Tib</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
